      ],
      "source": "https://katonahlibrary.org/about/our-history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1984 the Katonah Historical Museum opened on the library’s third floor, preserving local artifacts for visitors.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://katonahlibrary.org/about/our-history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Stepping Stones, the historic home of Alcoholics Anonymous founders Bill and Lois Wilson, is a National Historic Landmark in Katonah.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
